    <h1>6.1.1.1 Data Sharing Implementation</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"id-6.1.1.1DataSharingImplementation-AssetSharing">Asset S=
haring</h1>
<p>Currently already implemented...</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-6.1.1.1DataSharingImplementation-ItemSharing">Item Sharing</h1=
>
<p>The sharing implemenation is centered around a central database table <s=
trong>SharedItem&nbsp;</strong>with the following layout:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">ID: lon=
g (key)
DashboardId: nullable long (FK to Dashboard.ID)
ReportId: nullable long (FK to Report.ID)
FilterId: nullable long (FK to Filter.ID)
TargetEmail: nvarchar(255)
TargetUserId: nullable long (FK to User.ID)
AllowEdit: bit
EmailToken: nvarchar</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>The following data access business rules are reqiured:&nbsp;</p>
<p>(FilterID&nbsp;!=3D NULL)&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E2%8B%80" rel=3D"nofollow" style=3D"text-align: ce=
nter;">=E2=8B=80</a>&nbsp;(AllowEdit =3D=3D 1) =3D 0</p>
<p>(DashboardID =3D=3D NULL)&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E2%88%A8" rel=3D"nofollow" style=3D"text-align: ce=
nter;">=E2=88=A8</a>&nbsp;(FilterID =3D=3D NULL) =3D 1</p>
<p>(DashboardID =3D=3D NULL)&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E2%8B%80" rel=3D"nofollow" style=3D"text-align: ce=
nter;">=E2=8B=80</a>&nbsp;(FilterID =3D=3D NULL) =3D 0</p>
<p>(FilterID&nbsp;!=3D NULL)&nbsp; <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E2%8B%80" rel=3D"nofollow" style=3D"text-align: c=
enter;">=E2=8B=80</a>&nbsp;AllowEdit&nbsp; =3D 0</p>
<p>When a creating user shares an item with another user, a new row will be=
 added to the table SharedItem. In this row, the DashboardID/ReportID/Filte=
rID will be set to the ID of the item that's being shared. The TargetEmail =
field will be set to the emailadress of the recipient, the TargetUserId wil=
l be set to NULL, the AllowEdit bit will be set as specified by the sharing=
 user, the EmailToken will be set to the same dynamically generated cryptog=
raphically secure token that was used in the email, and the accepted bit wi=
ll be set to false.&nbsp;</p>
<p>When the receiving user clicks the link and logs in, the TargetUserId wi=
ll be set to his UserID.</p>
<p>When showing the list of user's dashboards/reports/filters, the filters =
that are shown are the filters that were created&nbsp; by the user and thos=
e that have a TargetUserId set to the current user. This is the same query =
that's used to determine if someone has access to a certain item.&nbsp;</p>
<p>When showing a certain item's shares, a query is performed for the curre=
nt item, and the TargetEmail, AllowEdit fields are shown. The system does n=
ot take into account whether or not the TargetUserId field is set. Nor is t=
he TargetUser's actual (system) email address shown.&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-6.1.1.1DataSharingImplementation-TokenHandling">Token Handling=
</h1>
<p>Tokens will not be generated as Guids as they are not cryptographically =
secure. They are generated with code similar to the following:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">using S=
ystem.Security.Cryptography;
...
using(RandomNumberGenerator rng =3D new RNGCryptoServiceProvider())
{
    byte[] tokenData =3D new byte[32];
    rng.GetBytes(tokenData);

    string token =3D Convert.ToBase64String(tokenData);
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p>A new controller ShareItemController will be developed that accepts thes=
e tokens. The controller will accept these tokens, look them up in the Shar=
edItem table etc.&nbsp;</p>
